## Verdict

**Do not commit/close P3-LR-RULE as-is.** The literature review is useful, broad, and mostly based on real sources, but three load-bearing conclusions are stronger than the cited evidence. Revise those before closing `kernel-of-truth-s55r.8` or creating P3-D-RULE.

## Three most important concerns

1. **“Matched compute” is incorrectly inferred from using the same model.**

   [RULE §2.3](</home/ec2-user/css/kernel/kernel-of-truth/docs/next/lit/RULE.md:206>) says compute is “matched by construction,” and the ledger labels CRANE “same model = matched compute.” That is false under Programme-3’s KOT-COST/2 standard. CRANE generates more tokens than unconstrained CoT in nearly every reported arm—e.g. 131.3 vs 129.0 at 1.5B and 235.8 vs 212.2 at 7B—and also performs constrained-decoder work. The paper reports accuracy gains, not a resource-matched frontier win. [CRANE results and token counts](https://arxiv.org/html/2502.09061)

   The same problem affects semantic monitors, backtracking, executor calls, and the extrapolation from XGrammar’s grammar-mask overhead to executor-derived masks. The correct claim is **same-host ablation**, not matched compute. Phase 1 must measure generated tokens, accelerator/CPU time, latency, energy, backtracking, and executor work against H-VL and the neural/RAG frontier.

2. **The “composition wall” is overgeneralized into a fundamental architectural law.**

   [RULE §5](</home/ec2-user/css/kernel/kernel-of-truth/docs/next/lit/RULE.md:384>) moves from controlled synthetic failures and an asymptotic bounded-depth theorem to:

   > rule application of depth ≥2 cannot be relied upon inside a frozen or lightly adapted forward pass

   and then classifies this as fundamental and capability-independent. The cited theory concerns constant-depth/log-precision transformers and particular arithmetic/equation constructions; it does not prove a general impossibility for finite-length rule tasks, latent recurrent mechanisms, deeper models, or trained adapters. [CoT theory paper](https://arxiv.org/abs/2305.15408) The Physics 3.2 result is real, but is explicitly a controlled synthetic knowledge-manipulation study, not a universal theorem about all rule composition. [Physics 3.2](https://arxiv.org/abs/2309.14402)

   This evidence supports a **strong prior and burden of proof**, not “fundamental; capability does not fix it.” Keep KV-of-rules and adapter-of-rules as falsifier arms alongside derived-fact variants; otherwise the review silently redefines away the placements it was asked to assess.

3. **The Phase-1 hand-off overstates both provenance and closure.**

   [RULE §6](</home/ec2-user/css/kernel/kernel-of-truth/docs/next/lit/RULE.md:433>) calls CD provenance “exact by construction.” An engine trace proves that a continuation was licensed and identifies supporting records. If several continuations remain valid, it does **not** prove why the LM chose one, nor does it provide provenance for unconstrained reasoning or uncovered spans. Call it exact **constraint/eligibility provenance**, with causal answer attribution only where the engine uniquely determines the span.

   The hand-off also lacks explicit acceptance/kill criteria for:

   - KOT-COST/2 and lifecycle accounting;
   - G1 coverage-ceiling;
   - matched generic RAG/tool-use and unconstrained post-check controls;
   - KV rule-premise versus derived-fact arms;
   - provenance sufficiency by span type;
   - dependencies on the shared frontier/index/hardware/NL-gate designs.

   The exported bead state still has P3-LR-RULE and P3-LR-NTP `in_progress`, and no P3-D-RULE exists. The document correctly acknowledges NTP as a co-blocker, but “this document, complete” is premature.

## Factual/citation issues

- **CRANE:** “matched compute” is incorrect. “Up to 10pp” is a paper-reported accuracy headline, but the arms have unequal output lengths and unaccounted decoding work. [CRANE](https://arxiv.org/html/2502.09061)
- **XGrammar:** near-zero grammar-transport overhead does not establish µs–ms overhead for semantic engines, per-token kernel calls, or backtracking.
- **PRAG ledger title:** `prag-2026` gives “Understanding Parametric Knowledge Injection in Retrieval-Augmented Generation”; the actual paper is **“The Role of Parametric Injection—A Systematic Study of Parametric Retrieval-Augmented Generation.”** Its substantive characterization is broadly correct. [PRAG paper](https://arxiv.org/abs/2510.12668)
- **VSA source pinning:** the 15.4×/88.6% figures are real in the EMNLP proceedings, but the ledger points to a mutable arXiv page whose current abstract reports different numbers. Pin the ACL Anthology publication. [EMNLP paper](https://aclanthology.org/2025.emnlp-main.1556/)
- **“Weight-space reliably fails under matched tests”:** RAG beating unsupervised fine-tuning is real, but the cited study does not establish matched lifecycle/tuning compute, and it tests knowledge injection—not rules. [Ovadia et al.](https://arxiv.org/abs/2312.05934)
- **“All CD caveats solved/mitigable”:** CRANE demonstrates a mitigation on GSM-Symbolic/FOLIO; it does not close distribution distortion, coverage-aware abstention, semantic-monitor cost, or arbitrary executor-coupled decoding.
- Eight records are explicitly `verified:false`; that is honestly disclosed, but `logic-lm-2023` is still used to frame the executor topology. Re-fetch it or remove its quantitative `+39.2%` from decision-bearing prose.
- There is a duplicated sentence at the start of §6.
- `verified:true` means only “URL fetched,” not claim-level verification. Add source version/date plus page/table/section locators for every quantitative or decision-bearing claim.

## Source reality assessment

I found **no clearly fabricated paper** among the spot-checked core sources. MGD, CRANE, AxBench, VSA-rule, KBLaM, AtlasKV, Memory Layers, Physics 3.2, Ovadia et al., and PRAG are real, and most headline descriptions are directionally accurate. For example, MGD really does report SantaCoder-1.1B exceeding text-davinci-003 on compilation and next-identifier match, while correctly remaining an unmatched cross-model comparison. [MGD](https://arxiv.org/abs/2306.10763)

The weakness is not wholesale hallucination; it is **claim-strength and accounting drift** beyond what those real papers establish.

**Decision: no-go as the final P3-LR-RULE commit.** After correcting compute language, downgrading the composition “wall” to a falsifiable prior, and strengthening the Phase-1 bead contract, it should be sound to commit.